39static void
40add_tl(kadm5_principal_ent_rec *princ, int type, krb5_data *data)
41{
42 krb5_tl_data *tl, **ptl;
43
44 tl = ecalloc(1, sizeof(*tl));
45 tl->tl_data_next = NULL;
46 tl->tl_data_type = type;
47 tl->tl_data_length = data->length;
48 tl->tl_data_contents = data->data;
49
50 princ->n_tl_data++;
51 ptl = &princ->tl_data;
52 while (*ptl != NULL)
53 ptl = &(*ptl)->tl_data_next;
54 *ptl = tl;
55
56 return;
57}
58
59static void
60add_constrained_delegation(krb5_context contextp,
61 kadm5_principal_ent_rec *princ,
62 struct getarg_strings *strings)
63{
64 krb5_error_code ret;
65 HDB_extension ext;
66 krb5_data buf;
67 size_t size = 0;
68
69 memset(&ext, 0, sizeof(ext));
70 ext.mandatory = FALSE;
71 ext.data.element = choice_HDB_extension_data_allowed_to_delegate_to;
72
73 if (strings->num_strings == 1 && strings->strings[0][0] == '\0') {
74 ext.data.u.allowed_to_delegate_to.val = NULL;
75 ext.data.u.allowed_to_delegate_to.len = 0;
76 } else {
77 krb5_principal p;
78 int i;
79
80 ext.data.u.allowed_to_delegate_to.val =
81 calloc(strings->num_strings,
82 sizeof(ext.data.u.allowed_to_delegate_to.val[0]));
83 ext.data.u.allowed_to_delegate_to.len = strings->num_strings;
84
85 for (i = 0; i < strings->num_strings; i++) {
86 ret = krb5_parse_name(contextp, strings->strings[i], &p);
87 if (ret)
88 abort();
89 ret = copy_Principal(p, &ext.data.u.allowed_to_delegate_to.val[i]);
90 if (ret)
91 abort();
92 krb5_free_principal(contextp, p);
93 }
94 }
95
96 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(HDB_extension, buf.data, buf.length,
97 &ext, &size, ret);
98 free_HDB_extension(&ext);
99 if (ret)
100 abort();
101 if (buf.length != size)
102 abort();
103
104 add_tl(princ, KRB5_TL_EXTENSION, &buf);
105}
106
107static void
108add_aliases(krb5_context contextp, kadm5_principal_ent_rec *princ,
109 struct getarg_strings *strings)
110{
111 krb5_error_code ret;
112 HDB_extension ext;
113 krb5_data buf;
114 krb5_principal p;
115 size_t size = 0;
116 int i;
117
118 memset(&ext, 0, sizeof(ext));
119 ext.mandatory = FALSE;
120 ext.data.element = choice_HDB_extension_data_aliases;
121 ext.data.u.aliases.case_insensitive = 0;
122
123 if (strings->num_strings == 1 && strings->strings[0][0] == '\0') {
124 ext.data.u.aliases.aliases.val = NULL;
125 ext.data.u.aliases.aliases.len = 0;
126 } else {
127 ext.data.u.aliases.aliases.val =
128 calloc(strings->num_strings,
129 sizeof(ext.data.u.aliases.aliases.val[0]));
130 ext.data.u.aliases.aliases.len = strings->num_strings;
131
132 for (i = 0; i < strings->num_strings; i++) {
133 ret = krb5_parse_name(contextp, strings->strings[i], &p);
134 ret = copy_Principal(p, &ext.data.u.aliases.aliases.val[i]);
135 krb5_free_principal(contextp, p);
136 }
137 }
138
139 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(HDB_extension, buf.data, buf.length,
140 &ext, &size, ret);
141 free_HDB_extension(&ext);
142 if (ret)
143 abort();
144 if (buf.length != size)
145 abort();
146
147 add_tl(princ, KRB5_TL_EXTENSION, &buf);
148}

150static void
151add_pkinit_acl(krb5_context contextp, kadm5_principal_ent_rec *princ,
152 struct getarg_strings *strings)
153{
154 krb5_error_code ret;
155 HDB_extension ext;
156 krb5_data buf;
157 size_t size = 0;
158 int i;
159
160 memset(&ext, 0, sizeof(ext));
161 ext.mandatory = FALSE;
162 ext.data.element = choice_HDB_extension_data_pkinit_acl;
163 ext.data.u.aliases.case_insensitive = 0;
164
165 if (strings->num_strings == 1 && strings->strings[0][0] == '\0') {
166 ext.data.u.pkinit_acl.val = NULL;
167 ext.data.u.pkinit_acl.len = 0;
168 } else {
169 ext.data.u.pkinit_acl.val =
170 calloc(strings->num_strings,
171 sizeof(ext.data.u.pkinit_acl.val[0]));
172 ext.data.u.pkinit_acl.len = strings->num_strings;
173
174 for (i = 0; i < strings->num_strings; i++) {
175 ext.data.u.pkinit_acl.val[i].subject = estrdup(strings->strings[i]);
176 }
177 }
178
179 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(HDB_extension, buf.data, buf.length,
180 &ext, &size, ret);
181 free_HDB_extension(&ext);
182 if (ret)
183 abort();
184 if (buf.length != size)
185 abort();
186
187 add_tl(princ, KRB5_TL_EXTENSION, &buf);
188}
189
190static void
191add_kvno_diff(krb5_context contextp, kadm5_principal_ent_rec *princ,
192 int is_svc_diff, krb5_kvno kvno_diff)
193{
194 krb5_error_code ret;
195 HDB_extension ext;
196 krb5_data buf;
197 size_t size = 0;
198
199 if (kvno_diff < 0)
200 return;
201 if (kvno_diff > 2048)
202 kvno_diff = 2048;
203
204 if (is_svc_diff) {
205 ext.data.element = choice_HDB_extension_data_hist_kvno_diff_svc;
206 ext.data.u.hist_kvno_diff_svc = (unsigned int)kvno_diff;
207 } else {
208 ext.data.element = choice_HDB_extension_data_hist_kvno_diff_clnt;
209 ext.data.u.hist_kvno_diff_clnt = (unsigned int)kvno_diff;
210 }
211 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(HDB_extension, buf.data, buf.length,
212 &ext, &size, ret);
213 if (ret)
214 abort();
215 if (buf.length != size)
216 abort();
217
218 add_tl(princ, KRB5_TL_EXTENSION, &buf);
219}
220
221static int
222do_mod_entry(krb5_principal principal, void *data)
223{
224 krb5_error_code ret;
225 kadm5_principal_ent_rec princ;
226 int mask = 0;
227 struct modify_options *e = data;
228
229 memset (&princ, 0, sizeof(princ));
230 ret = kadm5_get_principal(kadm_handle, principal, &princ,
231 KADM5_PRINCIPAL | KADM5_ATTRIBUTES |
232 KADM5_MAX_LIFE | KADM5_MAX_RLIFE |
233 KADM5_PRINC_EXPIRE_TIME |
234 KADM5_PW_EXPIRATION);
235 if(ret)
236 return ret;
237
238 if(e->max_ticket_life_string ||
239 e->max_renewable_life_string ||
240 e->expiration_time_string ||
241 e->pw_expiration_time_string ||
242 e->attributes_string ||
243 e->policy_string ||
244 e->kvno_integer != -1 ||
245 e->constrained_delegation_strings.num_strings ||
246 e->alias_strings.num_strings ||
247 e->pkinit_acl_strings.num_strings ||
248 e->hist_kvno_diff_clnt_integer != -1 ||
249 e->hist_kvno_diff_svc_integer != -1) {
250 ret = set_entry(context, &princ, &mask,
251 e->max_ticket_life_string,
252 e->max_renewable_life_string,
253 e->expiration_time_string,
254 e->pw_expiration_time_string,
255 e->attributes_string,
256 e->policy_string);
257 if(e->kvno_integer != -1) {
258 princ.kvno = e->kvno_integer;
259 mask |= KADM5_KVNO;
260 }
261 if (e->constrained_delegation_strings.num_strings) {
262 add_constrained_delegation(context, &princ,
263 &e->constrained_delegation_strings);
264 mask |= KADM5_TL_DATA;
265 }
266 if (e->alias_strings.num_strings) {
267 add_aliases(context, &princ, &e->alias_strings);
268 mask |= KADM5_TL_DATA;
269 }
270 if (e->pkinit_acl_strings.num_strings) {
271 add_pkinit_acl(context, &princ, &e->pkinit_acl_strings);
272 mask |= KADM5_TL_DATA;
273 }
274 if (e->hist_kvno_diff_clnt_integer != -1) {
275 add_kvno_diff(context, &princ, 0, e->hist_kvno_diff_clnt_integer);
276 mask |= KADM5_TL_DATA;
277 }
278 if (e->hist_kvno_diff_svc_integer != -1) {
279 add_kvno_diff(context, &princ, 1, e->hist_kvno_diff_svc_integer);
280 mask |= KADM5_TL_DATA;
281 }
282 } else
283 ret = edit_entry(&princ, &mask, NULL, 0);
284 if(ret == 0) {
285 ret = kadm5_modify_principal(kadm_handle, &princ, mask);
286 if(ret)
287 krb5_warn(context, ret, "kadm5_modify_principal");
288 }
289
290 kadm5_free_principal_ent(kadm_handle, &princ);
291 return ret;
292}
293
294int
295mod_entry(struct modify_options *opt, int argc, char **argv)
296{
297 krb5_error_code ret = 0;
298 int i;
299
300 for(i = 0; i < argc; i++) {
301 ret = foreach_principal(argv[i], do_mod_entry, "mod", opt);
302 if (ret)
303 break;
304 }
305 return ret != 0;
306}
